postcontent:
I have replaced the fire control group and moved it forward to proper configuration for an AK. It is made up of a Saiga/Vepr single stage Tapco G2, giving it an incredible tactile feel, it has been de burred and polished and was installed with the JTE Performance power hammer main spring.
It has a DPH Arms improved gas plug regulator and has the high reliability recoil spring and G2 performance puck that has been glass beaded and polished.
It has a modified bolt hold open lever to allow for easier disassembly during cleaning. 
The trigger guard has been replaced with the C.S.S. Billet Trigger guard designed to accept AR style lower grips. And currently sports a UTG Scorpion Grip. Very comfortable grip, it fills the palm and cushions well when shooting slugs. 
I have also added an extended magazine release that makes magazine changes much smoother than the stock configuration. 
The stock tang has been removed and replaced with a billet DPH internal stock block adapter with M4 style folding stock mechanism. This enables the ability to put any Mil-Spec AR style multi position stock on the Saiga. 
It has a billet quad rail for a forearm and has both a full length and short upper rail cover. It is not wearing either in the below photos. 
The vertical grip is an all aluminum grip and has a palm swell that fills the hand.
It sports a Phoenix Breach/Break on the barrel with break lock nut. 
Included are 6 SGM Tactical 10 round magazines plus the original 5 round.
I will be including all of the remaining original parts from the conversion as well. 
Please let me know if you have any interesting trades that would be equivalent to this setup.

title: For Sale:  Gemtech Subsonic .22LR Ammo
postcontent:
After years of recommending various brands and types of ammunition, we decided to do things right and create our own optimized round for suppressor usage. Putting together a heavier bullet, a cleaner powder, a premium lube on the lead round nose projectile gave us consistent velocities and harder hitting performance at subsonic, suppressor-friendly speed. The 42 grain lead round nose bullet is heavier than traditionally available rounds, but isn't so heavy as to cause instability. While "harder hitting" and ."22lr" aren't usually associated together, steel silhouette shooters will appreciate the difference between a knockdown and a wobbling target that stays up! A designed velocity of 1020 feet per second ensures the heavier projectile remains subsonic speed in most all firearms without resorting to anemic velocities. Our testing indicates that the ballistic coefficient for the 42gr GEMTECH bullet is approximately .125.

Sold in 500 round bricks, the GEMTECH SILENCER SUBSONIC .22lr ammunition is sub-packaged in 50 rd tray boxes to keep bullet noses from any accuracy-robbing damage during transit. Only five bricks left. Price posted is per brick. $10.00 extra for shipping.

title: For Sale:  LWRC M6 Individual Carbine AR-15 5.56 14.7" 1:7 IC
postcontent:
This is a brand new in box LWRC M6 Individual Carbine AR-15 semi automatic rifle chambered for 5.56mm NATO. The M6 Individual Carbine family is the direct descendant of the rifles developed by LWRC to meet the requirements of the U.S. Army Individual Carbine program. It includes some revolutionary new features while maintaining the basic M4/AR15/M16 architecture that has served our nation’s armed forces well for the past 40 years.

All members of the IC family feature a new fully ambidextrous lower receiver. Dual controls for bolt catch and release, magazine release, and fire control mean that both right- and left- handed shooters can use the rifle to its full effectiveness. In addition, dual controls give shooters the option of using their offhand side to accommodate barriers or injury. They can effectively manipulate the controls without having to switch hands. Despite its dramatically improved functionality, this new dual control lower receiver is compatible with all legacy AR15 pattern upper receivers.

The Monoforge upper receiver used in all members of the IC family is a further evolution of the M6A2-SPR platform introduced by LWRCI in 2011. It features a user-configurable rail system. Moreover, the mounting base for the handguard is machined as part of the upper receiver for added strength and reduced weight. The charging handle is also ambidextrous, to accommodate any operator.

LWRC rifles and carbines utilize cold hammer forged barrels made out of 41V45 steel alloy and treated with NiCorr surface conversion technology. Cold hammer forging takes an oversized barrel blank, and using high pressure rotary hammers, compacts the barrel blank over a mandrel. This forms perfect rifling devoid of tool marks. It also compacts the molecular structure of the metal making it denser and stronger. These barrels can take a lot more use and abuse than a standard barrel before any degradation in accuracy or loss of velocity.
